# Workflow Rules

## Pipeline Ordering (Immutable)

```
add_background_exc_inputs()   # MUST be first — creates synapses + bg spikes
  ↓
add_clustered_inputs()        # merges cluster stim onto existing bg spikes
  ↓
add_background_inh_inputs()   # tracks total exc activity — MUST be last
```

Rationale: inhibitory λ = FREQ_INH × total_exc_spikes / mean(total_exc_spikes).
Reordering breaks the E/I tracking coupling.

## Background Input Pipeline (Each Synapse)

```
pink_noise[random_trace]
  → rectify: negative → 0
  → rescale: mean → 1
  → Poisson(FREQ/1000 × pink_noise)
  → threshold: counts ≥ 1 → spike times
  → 50% dropout mask
  → spike_train_bg
```

Do not skip rectification, rescaling, or dropout — each is biophysically motivated.

## Cluster Stimulus Pipeline

```
generate_vecstim(rnd, unit_ids, num_stim, stim_time, var=5)
  → Normal(stim_time, 5) → floor → spike times per preunit
perm = rnd.permutation(num_preunit)
  → force first-cluster center preunit to perm[0]
  → activate perm[:k] for k in num_activated_preunit_list
```

## Output Directory Structure

Set via CLI `--results_root` (default `/G/results/simulation_singclus_supple_Jun26`). Full path:

```
{results_root}/
  {sec_type}_range{dis}_{spat}_{simu}{suffix}[_expected]/
    {folder_tag}/
      {epoch}/
        simulation_params.json
        section_synapse_df.csv
        preunit assignment.txt
        soma_v_array.npy
        dend_v_array.npy
        ... (all recording arrays)
        segment_nmda_spike_rate.npz  (if with_global_rec)
```

Downstream analysis scripts parse folder names via regex. Do not change the pattern.

## Coding Style

- Type annotations: not enforced yet, but add for new public functions.
- DataFrame access: prefer `.at[idx, col]` over `.loc[idx, col]` for scalar writes.
- NEURON objects: always `h.ClassName()`, never import from neuron submodules.
- Print statements for debugging (first 10 synapses) are intentional — do not remove.
- Commented-out code blocks are design alternatives — preserve them as documentation.
- Chinese comments (中文注释) are acceptable and present in codebase — do not translate.

## Weight Unit Conversion Checklist

When touching weight-related code, verify:
- [ ] Parameter input in µS (`initW`, `fixedW`)
- [ ] `section_synapse_df['syn_w']` written in nS (= 1000 × µS)
- [ ] `synapse.initW` set in µS
- [ ] `netcon.weight[0] = 1` is a switch, not a weight value

## Parallel Scheduling (`L5b_simulation.py`)

- Epoch sweep: `--num_epochs` + `--start_epoch` only (no `--epoch_mode`, `--num_batches`, `--epochs_per_batch`).
- Per `spat_cond` (serial): flatten `epoch × simu_cond × sec_type × dis_to_root` → one `ProcessPoolExecutor(max_workers_epoch)`.
- Per process: synapse/input prep uses `ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers_synapse)`; `h.run()` stays on main thread.
- `clus` must finish entirely before `distr` starts (same invocation: `--spat_cond clus distr`).
